<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 24 at 8:22AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow to impact travel in some areas through early this
evening...
Light snow will impact parts of north-central and southwest
Montana this morning through early this evening. Snow
accumulations will generally range from a trace to 1 inch, with
most areas likely to see less than one-half inch. The snow will
impact travel by reducing visibility at times and by causing slick
roads. Use caution and remember to allow yourself extra stopping
distance approaching turns, curves, and intersections.</description>
